kEqualsWithoutSubsumption(NodeType, NodeType, int, LinkedHashMap<NodeType, NodeType>) - Static method in class synoptic.algorithms.bisim.KTails
Without subsumption the children sets of both nodes must match each other exactly -- there needs to be a 1-1 correspondence that holds recursively.
kEqualsWithSubsumption(NodeType, NodeType, int) - Static method in class synoptic.algorithms.bisim.KTails
With subsumption its okay for some transitions of n1 to be unmatched with any transitions in n2, but all of n2 transitions must be matched to some transition in n1.
